gml:Dictionary.gml:description: Soil classification codes as defined by ASTM-D2487. These codes are used as values for the classificationCode property of the Lithology object.
gml:Dictionary.gml:name: DIGGS Soil Classification Codelist Definitions (ASTM D2487)

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; inorganic; LL ≥ 50; and PI plots above "A" line.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Fat clay

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; inorganic; LL < 50; PI> 7; and plots on or above "A" line.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Lean clay

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; liquid limit < 50; inorganic; plots in the hatched (CL-ML) zone in the plasticity chart.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silty clay

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits plot above "A" line and plasticity index greater than 7.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Clayey gravel

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits fall in hatched area marked CL-ML.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silty, clayey gravel

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits plot below "A" line and plasticity index <4.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silty gravel

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 5%; and not meeting Cu and Cc criteria for GW.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded gravel

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meets the criteria for GP and GC.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded gravel with clay (or silty clay)

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meets the criteria for GP and GM.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded gravel with silt

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve. passisng No. 200 screen <5%; Cu ≥ 4 and 1 ≤ Cc ≤ 3
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded gravel

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meets the criteria for GW and GC.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded gravel with clay (or silty clay)

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil on No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meets the criteria for GW and GM.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded gravel with silt

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; inorganic; LL ≥ 50; and PI plots below "A" line.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Elastic silt

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; inorganic; LL < 50; PI < 4, or plots below "A" line.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silt

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; organic; (LL for oven dried sample)/(LL for non dried sample) < 0.75; and LL ≥ 50.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Organic clay

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of soil passes No. 200 sieve; organic; (LL for oven dried sample)/(LL for non dried sample) < 0.75; and LL < 50.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Organic clay

diggs:Definition.gml:description: Peat, muck, and other highly organic soils.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Peat

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits plot above "A" line in the plasticity chart or plasticity index greater than 7.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Clayey sand

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits fall in hatched area marked CL-ML on the plasticity chart.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silty, clayey sand

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 > 12%; Atterberg's limits plot below "A" line in the plasticity chart or plasticity index less than 4.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Silty sand

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 < 5%; and not meeting both criteria for SW.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded sand

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meet she criteria for SP and SC.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded sand with clay (or silty clay)

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meet she criteria for SP and SM.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Poorly graded sand with silt

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 < 5%; Cu ≥ 6 and 1 ≤ Cc ≤ 3.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded sand

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meet she criteria for SW and SC.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded sand with clay (or silty clay)

diggs:Definition.gml:description: More than half of coarse soil passes No.4 sieve; passing No.200 is 5-12%; and meet she criteria for SW and SM.
diggs:Definition.gml:name: Well-graded sand with silt
